2.01</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_left\">10.5</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_left\">4.73</td>\n    <td style=\"background-color: #ECFDF5; color: #065F46;font-weight: bold;\" class=\"gt_row gt_right\">0.929</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_right\">2.27</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"gt_row gt_left gt_stub\">Difficult 3-way FE, N=10,000</th>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_left\">0.0094</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_left\">0.015</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_left\">0.026</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_right\">0.0090</td>\n    <td style=\"background-color: #ECFDF5; color: #065F46;font-weight: bold;\" class=\"gt_row gt_right\">0.0027</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"gt_row gt_left gt_stub\">Difficult 3-way FE, N=10,000,000</th>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_left\">382.9</td>\n    <td style=\"background-color: #ECFDF5; color: #065F46;font-weight: bold;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">3.25</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_left\">8.73</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_right\">32.7</td>\n    <td class=\"gt_row gt_right\">28.7</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n    <td style=\"color: #94A3B8;\" class=\"gt_row gt_left\">NB</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n  <tfoot class=\"gt_sourcenotes\">\n  \n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"gt_sourcenote\" colspan=\"11\"><strong>NB</strong> = not benchmarked (distinct from <code>fail</code>, which means the run hit its iteration limit without converging). Torch (CUDA) was not run on the Correia datasets, so those cells are <code>NB</code>. Stata was not run on the fixest DGP rows (Correia only published numbers for his 15 datasets), so those cells are <code>NB</code> too. Note that Torch (CUDA) and the Stata reference ran on different hardware than the local Python / R / Julia benchmarks.</td>\n  </tr>\n\n\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"gt_sourcenote\" colspan=\"11\">Local backends ran on a Mac mini (Apple M4, 10 cores, 16 GB RAM, macOS 15.3.1); Stata runtimes are reproduced from <a href=\"https://www.scorreia.com/data/hdfe/index.html\">Correia's website</a> and were obtained on different hardware. Tolerance is <code>1e-8</code> for every backend of the 'Correia data sets', else we use the package defaults.; convergence criteria differ across implementations.</td>\n  </tr>\n\n</tfoot>\n\n</table>\n\n</div>\n        \n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n::: {.callout-warning}\n## Reading the table\n\nCells that say `NB` indicate the cell was **not benchmarked** - we never ran that\nbackend on that dataset - and are distinct from `fail`, which means the backend ran\nto its iteration limit without converging at the requested tolerance. Torch (CUDA) was not run on the Correia datasets, so those cells are `NB`. Stata was not run on the fixest DGP rows (Correia only published numbers for his 15 datasets), so those cells are `NB` too. Note that Torch (CUDA) and the Stata reference ran on different hardware than the local Python / R / Julia benchmarks.\n:::\n\n## Reproducing these numbers\n\nTo run the benchmarks yourself, you can use the `pixi` tasks below, which will automatically install all required (open source) dependencies, create synethetic data sets and run the benchmarks. You will have to download the Correia datasets from [Correia's website](https://www.scorreia.com/data/hdfe/index.html) and place them in the `benchmarks/modular/data/correia` directory.\n\n```bash\n# benchmark fixest-dgp's\npixi run benchmark\n# benchmark R, Julia, Pyton on the Correia datasets\npixi run benchmark-correia\n```\n\n",
